w3ko, you did not try the best grouping. At level 2 and several levels above, a group of 3 will generally get the most XP/dinoz because at that level the group of 3 generally will encounted 2 or more enemies while a group of 1 or 2 will only see 1 enemy. [993635]
Does anyone know how the Defense values are formed.

I know that 1 element add 5 to assaults, but what is the effect in Defense?

Cheers,
On november 19, 2009
[None]
Defence is based upon the Grand Cycle of the Elements

Defence against = level + 1

Defense against element X = rating of X + 0.5*(ratings of the next two) + 1.5*(rating of prev. two) - the value is rounded as required.
e.g. Fire defense = + 0.5*( + )+1.5*( + )

There is no gauge of Clan respect but there is a Clan reputation.
All Clans currently have 0 reputation since reputation only applies during a Clan war and then, if a Clan has 0 reputation then it has 0 points and will be ranked last (with other 0 point clans) in the war.

Reputation has no other effect to a Clan.

[884682]
mfcata
Blazing Twilight will deal (fire element = 3 + lighthing element = 5) * 6 damage to every opponent (but I have to mention that you will have at least 7 elements of lightning when you will have Blazing Twilight..)

The damage of the powers or spells or A skills (whichever you prefer to call) is always based on the elements you have. If your dino makes a simple attack (hit) it is called "assault", which is based on the elements too (it is element * 5 + bonuses from fe. burning claws, etc.)

On december 25, 2009
[None]
@Jaaay9

Collecting skills (shown as type C, not P, A, etc.) collect different things in various places, depending on which collecting skill you have. There is one collecting set per element, and three levels per set. If you are in the right place for the skill you have you can see a grid from which you search a square. Additional skills let you search extra squares on that grid.

You can sell the things you find (Itinerant Merchant or Market) or donate them to a clan, once you have joined. When you have searched all squares in a grid, you get a bonus (around 1000 coins).

It is usual to train a Dinoz as a fighter or a collector, so you have some of each. If your level ups go wrong, you can change your training plan.

It is a big part of this game, and something else for you to learn and master.

Does Torch work with Counterattacks? Will the enemy receive damage from both skills?
On february 10, 2010
w3ko
If a dinoz with torch attacks and get counterattacked, torch skill will return damage to the counterattacker.

If a dinoz with torch get attacked but counterattacks, naturally it will return the torch damage first + the counterattack (its next element) damage.

Same with accupunture and those kind of skills.

[None]
What do you do with ingredients?
On february 10, 2010
Zephides
There are different things you can do with ingredients:
1) Trade with the Initerant Merchant for some gold (different places each week)
2) Trade with the Shady Man for some Treasury Notes (at the Tamer Market)
3) Donate to your clan, so they can built their castle and start a war or upgrades.
4) Some ingredients are used in Quests (such as the Kabuki Quest or the Elemental Teacher Quest).

[884682]
The can be used anytime to convert to 1.000 .

The price of the stuffs (dinoz, items, etc) depends only on the seller. Any price can be set, but there is minimum price for everithing. For dinoz , it depends on the cost of the dino plus its level. For an item or ingredients it is a fixed price. But the seller can put these on the market with any price at least the minimum.

f.e.
- amnestic rice: min 5.000
- 1st level gorilloz min 16.000+2000=18.000
- air element: min 1.000

etc.

rules on the market:
1. you have to put a package that has at least a combined minimum price of 5.000
2. you can set any price (minimum is the min. price of the package's total value.

Oh, and one more thing:

- It seems that petrification has been corrected: I've petrified a monster twice in a row, and the effect held on ...

On march 1, 2010
Piemaster
Groups don't do missions, individual dinos do missions. So if you group two dinos together and one has already completed the mission, the other one will be able to do it and the one who has already completed it can help (with most parts, see next paragraph) but the same dino can't do the same mission twice.

As for your second question certain parts of quests must be done solo, a good example being the buoy and climbing gear elementals. Typically fights that are triggered by an action outside your main game turn often/usually must be done solo, but there are exceptions.

Zephides
Fighter: any Dino with alot of A Skills. Such as a based Dino or based Dino. Speed and initiative is also important.

Defender: any Dino with alot of A Skills AND Sumo preferably. Speed and initiative is also important. Bubble is used often aswell.

(attackers and defenders are basicly the same, main difference is the amount of HP)

Gatherer: Dinoz with a high chance in the element of the gatherskill you want. Example: Moueffe for Fur Tuft, Glidwings for Energies.

Torch: The Dinoz is on fire.
Meaning: Every enemy that touches your Dino with be damaged by it. The more fire your Dino has, the more damage it will cause to your opponent.

Benediction: Gives the status Blessed to all Dinoz in the Group.
Meaning: I'm not sure about this, so correct me if I'm wrong. I believe the Dinoz will do slightly more damage when they are blessed.

How do I use the battle gear?
On march 28, 2010
Zephides
When you look into your inventory, behind some items are green arrows. If you click on those, the item will be moved to your Combat Gear.

The items will be randomly used in battle (no not always!).

Items that can be used in Combat Gear can be food, reinforcements and other boosts to your Dinoz.

On april 16, 2010
AndySQdancer
WerWolf, max level on any Dinoz is 50. If you reincarnate a Dinoz (have to have a special skill to do this), your Dinoz loses all the skills it learned and goes back to only the initial skill he was born/hatched with, but he gets an extra 5 random elements assigned to him for his troubles. Whether on not you choose all the basic skills depends on the Dinoz chances of getting skills in those elements (see our Clan pages for a list of the Dinoz and their chances of getting different elements). For some skills you want to take all the basic elements and grow in all trees. For other elements, you may only want to take one basic skill and take the skills in that tree. For other elements, you may want to build on two basic skill trees--it all depends on the Dinoz and how lucky you think you will be in getting different elements. However, Career Plan (a skill) can help you in developing your Dinoz.

AndySQdancer
Does the Itinerant Merchant only deal with ingredients?
-Can I exchange to ? or other way around?
-Is any other ways of useing besides buying stuffs from the market?
Yes, the Itinerant Merchant only buys ingredients for s (i.e. he pays you s for the basic ingredients he buys).

Changing s to is easy, just mouse click on the little hand to use them and the changes to 1K automatically.

Changing to s is no longer allowed to help prevent cheating.

Besides using s in the Market, they are required for some quest/missions and can be converted to .

On may 3, 2010
[None]
The defence value of an element is calculated from the value of all five elements and various skills.

For example, your Water defence is:

element + sum of defence bonuses from skills
+
0.5 * ( + sum of bonuses from skills)
+
0.5 * ( + sum of bonuses)
+
1.5 * ( + sum of bonuses)
+
1.5 * ( + sum of bonuses)

rounded to the nearest whole number
(+6 for the Hard-Boiled skill if it is a Demon Winks)


You can therefore easily see that a change in any element affects ALL defences and the Bao Charm affects ALL defences.

On may 8, 2010
MicEisvogel
Hey there =)

How do those spheres really work? Do you have to "use" them? and what will happen then? I heard that those increase the element by one and you will learn this special skill, but don't you need to level up first or will you gain this skill immediately?

Thanks in advance
On may 8, 2010
Zephides
Spheres will be stocked in your inventory. Click on the Dino you want to have Spheres and then click on the hand next to the Sphere.

The chosen Dino will receive a new skill accoring to what kind of sphere (and how many) he has. This will not add anything in your element built. If you have 5 lightning and add a lightning sphere, it will stay 5 lightning.

There are 3 different skills in total per Sphere-element.

So, if you'd pack 3 fire, 3 wood, 3 water, 3 lightning and 3 air spheres, you maximized all sphere skills on a Dino.

For example:
You put 1 lightning sphere on a Dino. This Dino will receive the Reflex skill. Then you choose to put another lightning sphere on the same Dino. He will also have the skill Sinuous Lightning now. Then, you decide to put a 3rd lightning sphere on him, he will have Survival now too. Now he has all the skills he can get with lightning spheres.

So you will receive the skill immediatly and you don't have to unlock anything.

You can look here to see what Air spheres there are for example. Click on the other skilltrees to see what the other element spheres have.

On june 2, 2010
AndySQdancer
Depending on the chance to get skills of a particular element should help you decide how many skills to take before unlocking. If you only have a few chances, you probably will only follow one skill tree. If you will get a lot for that element, you will probably follow 2 or 3 skill trees. Basic plan is not to use extra unlocks to get the skills you want. Wasted unlocks means wasted skills that you did not get.

Kayin
I've seen all your dinozs have long way before having the Lantern. You could always do the Strange Prowler mission(s) while you will got the required status items for the Hieroglyphics' mission.

- Then you got to dug out three status items.
--> Dig at the Swamp for the Swamp mud.
--> Dig at the Fountain of Youth for the Pure Water.
--> Dig at the Basalt Slopes for the Basalt Shard.
(Each time you dig something you got to repair the shovel by talking to the Coral Miner).

- You also got the Scorpscuba Caller, needed for going to the Underwater Dome. Talk to the Archsage and give him the three ingredients you dug out.
- You will fight the Earth Elemental. After winning the Archsage will give you the Zors Glove.
- Then go to Mutant Falls and talk to Master Hydargol. He will give you Waterlily Pads and you will be able to cross the falls to the Forest.
- Then go to the Haunted Hills and talk to the Strange Man. You will fight a korgon and win the Lantern.

You have to do it for each one of your dinoz.

On october 17, 2010
Stormy44
What is the difference between speed and initiative
On october 17, 2010
Asain
Each fighter has a value of time. The fighter with the smallest value performs an attack, then we add 10 / Speed at the time. So a fighter with 2.0 speed in attack twice more than 1.0 as fighting with each action will cost him 5 points of time instead of 10.

The Initiative will reduce the value of time at the beginning of combat. It therefore allows both to perform the first action, but also saves time over other fighters: a 10 DINOZE initiative with fighting a DINOZE with -10 will be almost certain to carry out two attacks before the other (since 20 points separate the time).

HERE is the thread for it.

On november 7, 2010
AndySQdancer
For E and A skills, do they all have the same chance of activating, or do they have separate chances? I've seen some A skills used a whole lot more than others, so I'm just curious.
ROBlNHOOD, each E and A Skills have their own chance of activation. The system checks each E and A Skills, starting at the highest level, working to the lowest level, until one of the Skills activates or all Skills have been checked. Don't know how the system chooses between Skills of the Same Level or betweek Elemental and Sphere Skills.

In answer to your pervious question about why both and -- It is to help prevent Cheating between Masters or Multi-Accounts (which are not allowed).

So pretty much, if a dinoz has Burning Breath, Mistral, and Water Cannon, and uses Burning Breath, then it can't use it again until it uses Mistral and WaterCannon?

Or if it has Focus, Wrath, and Good Whack, and it uses Focus, then it can't use Focus again until it uses Wrath and Good Whack?
On november 7, 2010
[895738]
No, it doesn't work that way, Robin. Remember, there is chance involved when it comes to A and E skills. However, as Andy said, they activate in the order of skill level (top to bottom). If you have 2 skills in the same skill level, then the chances for activating either of those skills is increased, but the chances of activating just one of the skills is decreased because the other skill infringes on that chance since you cannot activate 2 A skills at once. If you use burning breath, you may have a very small chance to use it again, but it's quite rare.
